to the editor re armed but not alarmed op ed march 21 richard ford is right on target when he says that an alliance between the conservation minded american hunter and the fear mongering paranoiacs running the nra is n't natural at all the recent statements by the national rifle association only highlight the desperation of an organization that receives so much criticism you need a license for fishing and driving but getting a gun from a gun show is not difficult at all president clinton is striving to close some of the loopholes in gun legislation but instead of cooperating the nra is on a futile mission to discredit him we can only hope that the presidential candidates will let the public know where they stand on gun control legislation john a varadarajan buffalo march 21 2000

